# Build context is the repo root for all service images. Exclude artifacts that
# must never be copied into a build: dependency trees (their symlinks point at
# host paths that don't exist in the container), framework build output, VCS and
# agent state, local env files, and logs. Keeping these out also shrinks the
# build context dramatically.

# Node / pnpm
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/.pnpm-store

# VCS and tooling state
.git
.github
.claude

# Local env and secrets (never bake into an image)
.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local

# Logs, coverage, OS cruft
**/*.log
**/coverage
**/.DS_Store

# Don't ship Dockerfiles/compose into the build context payload
**/Dockerfile.debug
